OL,3,CHorizon IT inquiry: Alan Bates says
OL,4,C'atrocious' Post Office is 'beyond
OL,5,Csaving'
OL,7,FProminent campaigner and former sub-
OL,8,Fpostmaster Alan Bates has called the
OL,9,FPost Office an "atrocious
OL,10,Forganisation" that's "beyond saving"
OL,11,Fand will be the "bugbear" of
OL,12,Fgovernment for years to come, in his
OL,13,Fevidence to the Horizon IT inquiry.
OL,15,FSpeaking from the witness box, Mr
OL,16,FBates accused the organisation of
OL,17,Fattempting to "discredit and silence"
OL,18,Fhim for more than two decades and
OL,19,F"definitely trying to outspend us" as
OL,20,Fpart of its "aggressive" tactics at
OL,21,Fthe High Court.
